mod_dnsblcheck allows you to configure one or more DNSBL servers to check incoming requests. 
It supports per-directory configuration and can limit DNSBL queries to specific HTTP methods 
(e.g. POST requests).

Examples

Per-Directory configuration: 
cat /etc/apache2/mods-enabled/dnsblcheck.conf 

<IfModule mod_dnsblcheck.c>
    DNSBLPrefix dnsbl1.domain
    DNSBLWhitelist 10.0.1.0/24
    DNSBLTestMethods POST
    DNSBLEngine off

    <Directory /var/www/mysiteA>
        DNSBLEngine on
    </Directory>

    <Directory /var/www/mysiteB>
        DNSBLEngine on
        DNSBLPrefix dnsbl1.domain dnsbl2.domain 
        DNSBLTestMethods POST PUT DELETE
    	DNSBLAction block
    	DNBLMessage "Blocked for SPAM"
        DNSBLHttpStatus 403
    </Directory>
</IfModule>
